  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gorenje Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Gorenje Group is the largest household appliance manufacturer in Southeast Europe and among the top 8 manufacturers of appliances in Europe. The Project involves (a) modernization, restructuring and expansion identified under the 2010-2013 strategic plan and (b) restructuring its debt maturing in 2010-2012.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The IFC investment will help Gorenje continue its longstanding leadership, by helping it expand, modernize, and restructure its operations following the economic crisis. The investment will result in better product competitiveness through improved energy efficiency and innovation, enhanced high end product range,  improved labor productivity  and  job creation in South-East region. The Groups investment program will allow the transfer of first-class production methods and manufacturing practices including the development of local industry through linkages with network of local suppliers. The capital increase associated with the Project will reduce the government&apos;s influence and strengthen market-oriented behaviors. Moreover, the IFC investment will support the Groups growing focus on ecology and offer comprehensive waste management solution to regional clients.</narrative>
  </description>
